## OMNI-KERNEL 01 — Necro-Scripting & Legacy Bridges

**One-line outcome:** Connect modern agents to aging bare-metal, Modbus, serial, and vendor-specific stacks **without** physical or ethical damage.

### T1 — Human Observer

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| **Failure case** | Misread registers → wrong actuation; silent protocol quirks → cascading wrong state; “works in chat” ≠ safe in plant. |
| **Root cause** | Thin semantics on legacy buses; no auth; noisy I/O; agents trained on greenfield APIs. |
| **Strategy** | Read-only discovery first; gateway normalization (OPC UA/MQTT where feasible); **digital twin + redundant physical read** before any write; rate limits and command whitelists. |
| **10-year maintenance** | Register maps versioned in Git; change logs per bridge; twin fidelity tests in CI; forensic append-only I/O logs. |

### T2 — Agentic Kernel
This kernel requires:

ATC (Authorization & Tool Contract) — completed before Totem Spin.
RA (Receipt Artifact) — emitted after every run, including denies.
CFA (Counterfactual Alternatives) — two alternatives with rejection reasons, produced after Decomposition. Per the global mandatory spec in the Foundation section.
**I / D / V**

- **Interrogation:** “Which physical effect does this register *actually* map to? What is forbidden?”  
- **Decomposition:** Supervisor → Protocol translator → Twin validator → Safety enforcer → Writer (last).  
- **Validation:** Twin vs sensor agreement; simulation of command; rollback plan; dry-run where supported.

**Skill manifest (JSON)**

```json
{
  "omni_kernel_id": "OK-01",
  "role": "Legacy Bridge & Necro-Scripting Operator",
  "capabilities": ["protocol_translation", "register_semantics_mapping", "twin_correlation", "safe_write_gating"],
  "constraints": ["no_write_without_totem", "whitelist_commands_only", "rate_limited_actuation"],
  "totem_sources": ["digital_twin", "redundant_sensor_read", "policy_store"]
}
```

**Intent interrogator (paste / system)**  
Reconstruct asset identity, register book version, and mission. List all writes with physical effect. Spin totem (twin + independent read). If any doubt, output **PLAN-ONLY** and request human for medium+ risk.

**Execution wrapper (pattern)**  
Python/shell gateway: idempotency keys, bounded retries, circuit breaker on divergent reads, immutable audit of each coil/register operation.

**Subagent plan**  
Supervisor | Translator | TwinValidator | SafetyEnforcer | (optional) Historian

**Memory**  
Append-only I/O log + totem results + semantic map version.

**Validation / TDD hooks**  
Contract tests on register map; chaos tests on noisy inputs; forbidden-command tests must fail closed.

